clinical_note: Horse, 8 years old, Thoroughbred. Lameness in left hind limb, heat and swelling in fetlock joint. Reluctant to bear weight. History of recent jumping competition.

Cat, 10 years old, Persian. Weight loss despite good appetite, increased urination and drinking. Blood glucose elevated at 18 mmol/L.
Bird, 2 years old, Cockatiel. Difficulty breathing, tail bobbing, open-mouth breathing. Crackling sounds on chest auscultation.
Cow, 5 years old, Holstein. Decreased milk production, fever 40.2Â°C, hard udder with clots in milk. Painful on udder palpation.
Dog, 2 years old, Labrador mix. Vomiting and diarrhea for 2 days, dehydration, abdominal pain. Owner reports garbage ingestion yesterday.
Cat, 4 years old, Maine Coon. Straining to urinate, blood in urine, frequent attempts with small volumes. Bladder feels enlarged and firm.
Rabbit, 3 years old, Holland Lop. Not eating pellets for 24 hours, soft stool, grinding teeth. Abdomen feels distended.
